<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900717-0002</DOCNO><DOCID>900717-0002.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing andamp; Media:   MGM/UA Receives   $53 Million as Part   Of Pathe Buy-Out Bid</HL><DATE>07/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9</SO><CO>   MGM PCC</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)</IN><LP>   CULVER CITY, Calif. -- MGM/UA Communications Co. said itreceived a $53 million payment from Pathe CommunicationsCorp. as part of Pathe's revised $1.3 billion acquisition ofthe once-mighty studio.   Last month, Pathe and MGM/UA revised and extended the$20-a-share proposed transaction, with Pathe agreeing to payMGM/UA shareholders an extra $1.50 a share. In the agreement,$4 of the $21.50 is to be paid out by July 20 to holders ofrecord July 10.</LP><TEXT>   Under the original tender offer, Pathe already haddeposited $200 million into an escrow account as a downpayment on the acquisition. The $53 million represents theremainder needed to make the interim $4 payment toshareholders, who will keep the money even if the dealcollapses. If it goes through, holders would get theremaining $17.50 in October.   The prior agreement between the two companies had beenbackstopped by a proposed $650 million loan by Time WarnerInc. to Pathe. That agreement fell apart, Pathe and TimeWarner have sued each other, and Pathe is looking for newsources of financing.   MGM/UA also said that according to a ruling by the NewYork Stock Exchange, MGM/UA shares had been trading on thebasis of one share of stock plus a &quot;due bill&quot; of $4 sinceJuly 3. It is expected that the stock will begin trading&quot;ex-payment&quot; one business day following the payment date, thecompany said.   The latest payment brings to $253 million the amount Pathehas advanced toward the transaction since last March. Pathehas also given MGM/UA a $75 million security interest inthree upcoming Pathe films. According to the revisedagreement, Pathe must deposit $50 million payments on Aug. 21and Sept. 20.</TEXT></DOC>